New Records: England - 329 for 5 vs West Indies in North Sound in 2024*
Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone reached to the fifty in 60 balls and then took only 17 balls more to bring up his first ODI hundred
England eventually surpassed the West Indies' total with 15 balls to spare, winning the match by five wickets
Post-Match Reflections: Stand-in captain Liam Livingstone said his hard work over the last few months has started paying off.
Simply BRILLIANT! A first ODI 100 for @liaml4893, and at the perfect time!
Miscellaneous Highlights: Livingstone's acceleration in the latter part of the innings was unbelievable.

Certain things I have done in practice and at the end of the season in England felt like I have been getting back to my best. Maturing and I'm enjoying my cricket and if I'm enjoying my cricket, I play well. Pretty proud day,
